A lady identified as Martha Uche has volunteered to donate her kidney to Sonia, the ailing daughter of former Deputy Senate President, Ike Ekweremadu. The Nation reports London Metropolitan Police charged Ekweremadu and Beatrice, his wife, to court over the allegation of bringing a child to the UK for organ harvesting. The investigation was launched after detectives were alerted to potential offences under modern slavery legislation in May 2022.   NCPC boss to Pilgrims: Practice what you have learnt from…     MSII SDG Initiative calls for applications     European Union partners NGO to fight malnutrition, poverty   The UK authorities said the “child” had “been safeguarded”, while the police added that its operatives “are working closely with partners on continued support”. In the now-viral video obtained by The Nation, Martha said she saw it in her dream that she needs to help the ailing child of the former Deputy Senate President. Speaking on why she wants to donate her kidney, Martha said: “I need to help the girl. She is dying. They have already shown me in my dream that I should help the girl. “I have already seen it a long time ago. They have already shown me in my dream. I need to do this fast “I don’t have any demands, for now, I’m ready to save the girl’s life. That’s the most important thing.”